			<div class="dr-title-wrap">
				<h2 class="dr-title recipe-card-title">Easy Basic Pancakes Recipe</h2><div class="dr-entry-meta"><span class="dr-byline"><span class="dr-meta-title">
					<svg class="icon"><use xlink:href="https://stewartrecipes.com/wp-content/plugins/delicious-recipes/assets/images/sprite.svg#author"></use></svg>Author: </span>Nell</span><span class="dr-method"><span class="dr-meta-title"><svg class="icon"><use xlink:href="https://stewartrecipes.com/wp-content/plugins/delicious-recipes/assets/images/sprite.svg#cooking-method"></use></svg> Cooking Method:</span><a href="javascript:void(0);" title="Griddle">Griddle</a></span><span class="dr-cuisine"><span class="dr-meta-title"><svg class="icon"><use xlink:href="https://stewartrecipes.com/wp-content/plugins/delicious-recipes/assets/images/sprite.svg#cuisine"></use></svg> Cuisine:</span><a href="javascript:void(0);" title="American">American</a></span><span class="dr-category"><span class="dr-meta-title"><svg class="icon"><use xlink:href="https://stewartrecipes.com/wp-content/plugins/delicious-recipes/assets/images/sprite.svg#category"></use></svg> Courses:</span><a href="javascript:void(0);" title="Breakfast">Breakfast</a></span><span class=""><span class="dr-meta-title"> </span></span></div></div></div>
					<div class="dr-extra-meta"><span class="dr-sim-metaa dr-lavel"><span class="dr-meta-title"><svg class="icon"><use xlink:href="https://stewartrecipes.com/wp-content/plugins/delicious-recipes/assets/images/sprite.svg#difficulty"></use></svg> Difficulty:</span><b>Beginner</b></span><span class="dr-sim-metaa"><span class="dr-meta-title"><svg class="icon"><use xlink:href="https://stewartrecipes.com/wp-content/plugins/delicious-recipes/assets/images/sprite.svg#time"></use></svg>Prep time:</span><b> 10 minutes</b></span><span class="dr-sim-metaa"><span class="dr-meta-title"><svg class="icon"><use xlink:href="https://stewartrecipes.com/wp-content/plugins/delicious-recipes/assets/images/sprite.svg#time"></use></svg>Cook time:</span><b> 10 minutes</b></span><span class="dr-sim-metaa"><span class="dr-meta-title"><svg class="icon"><use xlink:href="https://stewartrecipes.com/wp-content/plugins/delicious-recipes/assets/images/sprite.svg#time"></use></svg>Rest time:</span><b> minutes</b></span><span class="dr-sim-metaa"><span class="dr-meta-title"><svg class="icon"><use xlink:href="https://stewartrecipes.com/wp-content/plugins/delicious-recipes/assets/images/sprite.svg#time"></use></svg>Total time:</span><b> 20 minutes</b></span><span class="dr-sim-metaa"><span class="dr-meta-title"><svg class="icon"><use xlink:href="https://stewartrecipes.com/wp-content/plugins/delicious-recipes/assets/images/sprite.svg#yield"></use></svg>Servings:</span><b>4 servings</b></span><span class="dr-sim-metaa"><span class="dr-meta-title"><svg class="icon"><use xlink:href="https://stewartrecipes.com/wp-content/plugins/delicious-recipes/assets/images/sprite.svg#calories"></use></svg>Calories:</span><b>200 kcal</b></span><span class="dr-sim-metaa dr-season"><span class="dr-meta-title"><svg class="icon"><use xlink:href="https://stewartrecipes.com/wp-content/plugins/delicious-recipes/assets/images/sprite.svg#season"></use></svg> Best Season:</span><b>Available</b></span></div><div class="dr-summary recipe-card-summary"><h3 class="dr-title summary-title">Description</h3><p>A classic, foolproof recipe for light and fluffy homemade pancakes that are perfect for a weekend breakfast.</p></div>
					<div class="dr-ingredients-list"><div class="dr-ingrd-title-wrap wpg-gap-1"><h3 class="ingredients-title dr-title">Ingredients</h3></div><ul class='ingredients-list dr-unordered-list '><li><input type="checkbox" id="dr-ing-ingredient-item-68a375b6ee064"/><label for ="dr-ing-ingredient-item-68a375b6ee064"><span class="dr-ingredient-name">1 cup all-purpose flour</span></label><li><input type="checkbox" id="dr-ing-ingredient-item-68a375b6ee065"/><label for ="dr-ing-ingredient-item-68a375b6ee065"><span class="dr-ingredient-name">2 tbsp sugar</span></label><li><input type="checkbox" id="dr-ing-ingredient-item-68a375b6ee066"/><label for ="dr-ing-ingredient-item-68a375b6ee066"><span class="dr-ingredient-name">2 tsp baking powder</span></label><li><input type="checkbox" id="dr-ing-ingredient-item-68a375b6ee067"/><label for ="dr-ing-ingredient-item-68a375b6ee067"><span class="dr-ingredient-name">&#xBD; tsp salt</span></label><li><input type="checkbox" id="dr-ing-ingredient-item-175554335462215"/><label for ="dr-ing-ingredient-item-175554335462215"><span class="dr-ingredient-name">1 cup milk</span></label><li><input type="checkbox" id="dr-ing-ingredient-item-175554335540616"/><label for ="dr-ing-ingredient-item-175554335540616"><span class="dr-ingredient-name">2 tbsp melted unsalted butter</span></label><li><input type="checkbox" id="dr-ing-ingredient-item-175554335579017"/><label for ="dr-ing-ingredient-item-175554335579017"><span class="dr-ingredient-name">1 large egg</span></label></ul></div><div class="dr-instructions"><div class="dr-instrc-title-wrap"><h3 class="directions-title dr-title">Instructions</h3></div><ol class="directions-list dr-ordered-list"><li>Whisk together the flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt in a small bowl.</li><li>In a medium bowl, whisk together the milk, melted butter, and egg.</li><li>Pour the dry ingredients into the wet ingredients and whisk until just combined (a few lumps are okay).</li><li>Heat a lightly oiled griddle or skillet over medium heat.</li><li>Pour 2 to 3 tablespoons of batter per pancake onto the griddle.</li><li>Cook for 1-2 minutes per side, flipping once bubbles start to pop on the surface.</li><li>Serve immediately with your favorite toppings.</li></ol><!-- Ezoic - wp_longest_content - longest_content --><div id="ezoic-pub-ad-placeholder-132" data-inserter-version="2" data-placement-location="longest_content"></div><script data-ezoic="1" data-no-optimize="1" data-no-defer="1">ezstandalone.cmd.push(function () { ezstandalone.showAds(132); });</script><!-- End Ezoic - wp_longest_content - longest_content --></div><div class="dr-note">
					<h3 class="dr-title notes-title">Notes</h3>
					<ul class="recipe-card-notes-list"><li>The most important tip for fluffy pancakes is not to overmix the batter.</li><li>For perfectly round pancakes, use the back of your spoon to gently spread the batter after pouring it.</li><li>Keep cooked pancakes warm in a 200&#xB0;F oven on a baking sheet while you finish the batch.</li><li>This recipe is easily adaptable with buttermilk or whole grains (see variations above).</li></ul>
				</div><div class="dr-keywords"><span class="dr-meta-title">Keywords:</span>Easy Basic Pancakes Recipe</div><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https:\/\/schema.org","@type":"Recipe","name":"Easy Basic Pancakes Recipe","image":"","description":"A classic, foolproof recipe for light and fluffy homemade pancakes that are perfect for a weekend breakfast.","keywords":["Easy Basic Pancakes Recipe"],"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Nell"},"datePublished":"2025-08-18T19:01:41+00:00","prepTime":"PT10M","cookTime":"PT10M","totalTime":"PT20M","recipeCategory":["Breakfast"],"recipeCuisine":["American"],"cookingMethod":["Griddle"],"recipeYield":["4","4 servings"],"nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"200 cal"},"recipeIngredient":["1 cup all-purpose flour","2 tbsp sugar","2 tsp baking powder","\u00bd tsp salt","1 cup milk","2 tbsp melted unsalted butter","1 large egg"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"Whisk together the flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt in a small bowl.","text":"Whisk together the flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt in a small bowl.","url":"https:\/\/stewartrecipes.com\/easy-basic-pancakes-recipe\/#delicious-recipes-direction-step-68a375b6ee069","image":""},{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"In a medium bowl, whisk together the milk, melted butter, and egg.","text":"In a medium bowl, whisk together the milk, melted butter, and egg.","url":"https:\/\/stewartrecipes.com\/easy-basic-pancakes-recipe\/#delicious-recipes-direction-step-68a375b6ee06a","image":""},{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"Pour the dry ingredients into the wet ingredients and whisk until just combined (a few lumps are okay).","text":"Pour the dry ingredients into the wet ingredients and whisk until just combined (a few lumps are okay).","url":"https:\/\/stewartrecipes.com\/easy-basic-pancakes-recipe\/#delicious-recipes-direction-step-68a375b6ee06b","image":""},{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"Heat a lightly oiled griddle or skillet over medium heat.","